How about

``` rust
pub struct Ident {
    name: Name,
    ctxt: SyntaxContext,
    kind: IdentKind
}

pub enum IdentKind {
    PlainIdent,
    LifetimeIdent
}
```

Will this somehow intervene with codegen, which I haven't had a chance to look into?

@jbclements I probably am using it differently. I think I should just remove the "fully", and say "lifetimes are in a separate namespace and are hygienic".

> I do think we should think hard about exactly what programs are ruled out by putting loop identifiers and ordinary bindings into the same bucket.

Hm... I haven't used true scheme-y macros enough to really say much (so I don't even know why I'm here... ;P ). Are any programs ruled _in_ by having them in the same bucket?
